messages.content:
Now let me count the medals by format to determine which format(s) Goh Soon Huat is most successful in. I'll need to join these tables and count medals by format name, potentially weighing them by type (Gold > Silver > Bronze).

Let me first create a query to count medals by format:

function.arguments:
{"command": "psql -c "
SELECT 
    f.name AS format_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalGold' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS gold_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalSilver' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS silver_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalBronze' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS bronze_medals
FROM athlete a
JOIN tournament t ON a.athlete_id = t.athlete_id
JOIN format f ON t.tournament_id = f.tournament_id
JOIN medal m ON f.format_id = m.format_id
WHERE a.name = 'Goh Soon Huat'
GROUP BY f.name
ORDER BY total_medals DESC, gold_medals DESC, silver_medals DESC;
""}
function.name: bash

actions.command:
psql -c "
SELECT 
    f.name AS format_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalGold' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS gold_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalSilver' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS silver_medals,
    SUM(CASE WHEN m.type = 'MedalBronze' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS bronze_medals
FROM athlete a
JOIN tournament t ON a.athlete_id = t.athlete_id
JOIN format f ON t.tournament_id = f.tournament_id
JOIN medal m ON f.format_id = m.format_id
